 10  # Basic logic properties
 11  
 12  This file is one of the earliest imports in mathlib.
 13  
 14  ## Implementation notes
 15  
 16  Theorems that require decidability hypotheses are in the namespace "decidable".
 17  Classical versions are in the namespace "classical".
 18  
 19  In the presence of automation, this whole file may be unnecessary. On the other hand,
 20  maybe it is useful for writing automation.
 21  -/

628  library_note "classical lemma"
629  "We make decidability results that depends on `classical.choice` noncomputable lemmas.
630  * We have to mark them as noncomputable, because otherwise Lean will try to generate bytecode
631    for them, and fail because it depends on `classical.choice`.
632  * We make them lemmas, and not definitions, because otherwise later definitions will raise
633    \"failed to generate bytecode\" errors when writing something like
634    `letI := classical.dec_eq _`.
635  Cf. <https://leanprover-community.github.io/archive/113488general/08268noncomputabletheorem.html>"
636
